Business Brief -- PNP Holdings Corp.:
   Unit to Shut Nine Stores,
   Fire 10% of Work Force
Separately, Pay 'N Pak, a subsidiary of PNP Holdings
Corp., said in June it plans to fire 30 workers in its head
office. The company also said it appointed Alfred J. Koontz
Jr. as chief financial officer. Mr. Koontz, who previously
served in a similar position at Seattle's Todd Shipyards
Corp., succeeds Gregory B. Maffei, who remains an executive
vice president and a member of the board.